properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 18 at 2:47PM CST until February 19 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS TONIGHT ACROSS MUCH OF NORTHEAST
MINNESOTA...

.Dangerous wind chills are expected across much of northeast
Minnesota tonight. Wind chill values will range from 20 to 30
degrees below zero as an Arctic airmass settles over the region.
Frost bite is possible in as little as 30 minutes.

* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as
25 below zero.

* WHERE...Koochiching, North St. Louis, Northern Cook and Lake,
North Itasca, Central St. Louis, North Cass, South Itasca and
South Cass Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the
Bois Forte Band, Deer Creek, Nett Lake and, Lake Vermillion
areas.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 10 AM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 10 AM CST WEDNESDAY
